entries.title: The FAA NOTAM Outage Highlights an Essential System Everyone Hates
entries.description: A glitch in the so-called NOTAM system caused the agency to ground flights across the US. But its problems go back years.

entries.title: As Gig Economy Companies Flee Europe, Getir Is Taking Over
entries.description: Rapid grocery delivery apps are leaving the continent, putting the Turkish startup on top. But, its reign is anything but stable.

entries.title: FTX Has Wrecked the Crypto Party in Paradise
entries.description: The digital currency exchange’s stupendous fallout has put local Web3 companies in the Bahamas on the back foot.
